We can use the `googlesheets4` package to make quick Google Sheet dashboards. 
Lets spin up a quick Google Sheet dashboard using the breweries dataset from 
`mappview`.

```{r}
library(googlesheets4)
library(dplyr)

data("iris")

iris |> 
  head()
```

We can use `sheet_write()` to add the data to a new sheet in the Google Sheet. By default, 
the data is added to a new sheet sharing the same name as the dataset. We can use the 
`sheet` argument to specify a specific sheet. Lets first make a sheet named `data` 
and add our data to the sheet.

```{r}
ss = "https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Lph7x76HCzpf1blROG-XabhEywtB72R8V5iYCCnch0w/edit#gid=0"

# googlesheets4::sheet_add(ss, sheet = "data")

iris |> 
  googlesheets4::sheet_write(ss, sheet = "data")

```

See the [Google Sheet here:](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Lph7x76HCzpf1blROG-XabhEywtB72R8V5iYCCnch0w/edit#gid=0). 

From here, we can take our data and make a dashboard built on the latest data sent to the Google Sheet. 


